2026-04-16 11:09:43 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Relay contacts in control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The control module output voltage drops to approximately 0.36 V during the flicker event, while the input voltage remains steady at nearly 12 V. The relay was visually inspected and appeared to be closed, yet the output voltage is significantly lower than the input—a symptom consistent with high resistance or intermittent connection at the relay contacts, even when visually closed. Given the relay directly switches the output, a degraded contact or partial failure could allow some voltage to pass but not enough current to properly drive the lamp, causing the cycling off/on behavior. Visual inspection does not always catch internal contact degradation.'
